frameDefinitions: An Agent works on a Project so that it reaches a more advanced and desirable state.
An Agent or Cause causes a Process or State to continue.
The Creator creates a new entity, the Created_entity, possibly out of Components.
A Producer produces a Product from a Resource for commercial purposes. '
A person (Speaker) expresses a Message or mental content, broadly understood, in a particular Manner.
An Developer develops a Product, in some cases for a Company.    '' 'The development of a profitable product will be necessary for the company to stay afloat.
frameExamples: The goaltenders <t>kept</t> the game going with terrific saves.
The Libyans were <t>generating</t> arms for export.
They <t>produced</t> only half of the units after an injunction to follow the environmental policy.
The <t>development</t> of a profitable product will be necessary for the company to stay afloat. INI
listRoleDefinitions: The object or idea that undergoes change due to the efforts of the <fen>Agent</fen>.
The individual that brings about the development of the <fen>Project</fen>.
The time at which the progress occurs.
The location at which the the <fen>Project</fen> progresses.
The individual who causes the <fen>Process</fen> to continue or the <fen>State</fen> to be maintained.
A <fen>Process</fen> that is maintained by the <fen>Agent</fen> or <fen>Cause</fen>.
The <fen>State</fen> that is maintained by the <fen>Agent</fen> or <fen>Cause</fen>.
An event that causes the <fen>Process</fen> or <fen>State</fen> to be maintained.
The time at which the <fen>Process</fen> continues.
The location at which the <fen>Process</fen> continues.
The Creator creates a created entity.
This role identifies the entity that the Agent intentionally creates.
This role identifes the Time when an Agent intentionally creates a new entity.
This role identifies the place ehere the Agent intentionally creates the new entity.
The person or company that produces the Product.
The <fen>Product</fen> is produced by the <fen>Producer</fen>.
<fen>Factory</fen> identifies the particular plant where the <fen>Product</fen> is manufactured.
This Fe identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the product was produced.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Product</fen> is manufactured.
<fen>Speaker</fen>, the person who encodes the <fen>Message</fen>, occurs as the External Argument of all the verbs:
The <fen>Message</fen> is almost invariably expressed in an NP Object. (The only exceptions occur with the verb <t>express</t>, which is occasionally used with that-clause complements.)

For most of the words in this frame, some expression of <fen>Manner</fen> or <fen>Medium</fen> is obligatory. As in other frames, <fen>Manner</fen> expressions characterize the action (in this case, the speech act performed by the <fen>Speaker</fen>). However, a wide range of <fen>Manner</fen> expressions occurs in this frame, including the following types:
<fen>Medium</fen> expresses the <fen>Medium</fen> of communication, such as the language used or the specific type of text in which the <fen>Message</fen> occurs:
The person who develops the <fen>Product</fen>.
The entity which is developed by the <fen>Developer</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Product</fen> is developed by the <fen>Developer</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Product</fen> is developed by the <fen>Developer</fen>.
